<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Thorling:
[B]At 26 I still solo a little.  AC all the way -- I still pull out my melange of bronze, fine plate, and that sort of stuff.  Call me wierd, but I love going toe-to-toe using yaulp II, flash of light, and the odd smite or dismiss undead as mana allows.  

But when I group, I put all that stuff away and put on my wis jewelry.  Right now I am the emergency first aid kit for a well-tuned 31 Druid / 35 Ranger Hill Giant assassination team.  When things go well, they don't need me at all.  But they share exp and plat with me because things don't always go well.   :)  I feel terribly naked without my armor on, especially if I mess up and get doubletapped by one of those big giants before Brunred or Redbrun can get snare and root to stick.  Dang that smarts!  But when they need me, they need every last heal I can pump out, and they keep  nagging me to buy more wisdom items.  If I "forget" to take off my armor, they remind me, heh.

-- Thorling, 26th Gnome Cleric of Bristlebane on Tribunal[/B][/QUOTE]

