<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jacob</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">   I got the Supple Scale Armband from KC last night. When worn it drops my AC by 10 but gives me 25 more mana and +10 sv fire. I dont know which I should wear. <BR>Cleric bracer is 9ac 5wis<BR>Supple Scale Armband 3ac 5wis 5int 25mana 10 sv fire.<BR>Which is better more AC or more Mana? I am level 51.<P>Jake<BR>Level 51 Vicar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aenae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">AC.  Until you get your unbuffed AC to 1000, go with AC every time over raw mana.<P>That being said, I have an armband also.  Makes great resist gear vs Talendor.<P>- Aenae Webspinner</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I too got one of those last night, and went ahead and replaced my bracer of rev with it. I did it because I only have 178 wis so the extra 25 mana is a big help. If I had to decide between a EM bracer and this one, I'd stick with the EM. Em has higher AC. All you really lose is the +10vs fire. Then you just keep the supple for those naggy raids where you'll want the higher resists.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kannayyan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">heres my take...my 22 cleric is outfitted with WIS and mana over Ac so far...why?<P>first of all, when I want to solo, I simply play my necro, not my cleric. I group with the same people with my cleric over and over. Anyone knows that the two most hated people in a group fighting environment are the one who does the most damage, or most notably, a chanter or healer.....In my experience so far, my chanter gets beat up way more than I do, so we have outfitted him with a little more AC than myself. We find that this works well...while he gets pounded, I can chain stun a mob until he can mezz again(or root if necessary) and can also heal my tanks. Usually if Im getting pounded hard, I will spam for the nuker to start dropping bombs and pull the aggro off me or I will simply cast grim aura, run a safe distance, and grab some popcorn and watch the rest of the fight play off. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zellidon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmm I'm lvl 60 and I choose HP/Mana over AC/Mana.  No matter how high AC you have when you get to lvl 60 you'll be fighting mainly mobs that will smack you for probably max damage everytime.  HP items are much more effective I wear a Djarn's Ring, Velium Fire Opal (nice ac too), BS Neck for the mana/hp.  And I can get about 2850 hp self buffed which isn't too bad for a dark elf.  So if I had to choose between an item that had 5 more ac than an item that gave +25 hp I'd choose the +25 hp =).<P>------------------<BR>Zellidon Soulifter<BR>60 Dark Priest of Innoruuk<BR>The Seventh Hammer</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zellidon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Also have 985 ac too so yes I do like to have high AC too to back me up hehe.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kraphalis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kannayyan, you'll like AC a lot when you get to the point where you kick off a complete heal and the mob you are fighting doubles, triples, or quadruples for HP in the triple digits.  In the higher levels, there are things that can kill you in one round.<P>I used to be WIS over AC.  And I think in the lower levels you can safely get away with that.<P>Now, I'm working on my AC, and sacrificing a little WIS.  I'm back up to 193 WIS with 800 AC.  Still low AC, but my cleric doesn't have lotsa money or time to camp stuff.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thorling</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">At 26 I still solo a little.  AC all the way -- I still pull out my melange of bronze, fine plate, and that sort of stuff.  Call me wierd, but I love going toe-to-toe using yaulp II, flash of light, and the odd smite or dismiss undead as mana allows.  <P>But when I group, I put all that stuff away and put on my wis jewelry.  Right now I am the emergency first aid kit for a well-tuned 31 Druid / 35 Ranger Hill Giant assassination team.  When things go well, they don't need me at all.  But they share exp and plat with me because things don't always go well.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  I feel terribly naked without my armor on, especially if I mess up and get doubletapped by one of those big giants before Brunred or Redbrun can get snare and root to stick.  Dang that smarts!  But when they need me, they need every last heal I can pump out, and they keep  nagging me to buy more wisdom items.  If I "forget" to take off my armor, they remind me, heh.<P>-- Thorling, 26th Gnome Cleric of Bristlebane on Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sanctume</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">As long as I have 200 wis, I have plenty of mana to heal.<P>Depends on the mob.  <P>If against AoE casting mobs, I try to get +200 on specific resist.  RP for Trak, etc...<P>If doing normal melee mobs, I go for AC.<P>If doing melee mobs such as velk... might as well go +Mana since you're dead in 3 seconds if they notice you.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zellidon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm telling you, you'll want the HP more at 60 =)<P>------------------<BR>Zellidon Soulifter<BR>60 Dark Priest of Innoruuk<BR>The Seventh Hammer</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rizena Halcyon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>Umm, Dikmer -- The EM bracer is AC 9 which is exactly the same as the Bracer of the Reverant, how do you figure that's an AC upgrade?  Now if you're talking Donals, I totally agree  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P><BR>To Jake,<BR>   I'd personally go with AC first then mana.  I RARELY get the chance to start any fights at full mana, so the extra mana items don't really help.  I do get smacked down pretty hard while I heal the incoming tank and wait for the fight to get under control.  There's no way 6 AC is worth 25 mana.  I'd definitely keep the armband though (even if it wasn't no drop) just because it is nice resist gear.<P><BR>Rizena Halcyon<BR>Templar of the Mithril Tower<BR>Ayonae Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kannayyan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Kraphalis:<BR><B>Kannayyan, you'll like AC a lot when you get to the point where you kick off a complete heal and the mob you are fighting doubles, triples, or quadruples for HP in the triple digits.  In the higher levels, there are things that can kill you in one round.<BR></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Like I said earlier, if you are in a group and you are being hit for several rounds, you are probably in a pretty lame group. If a group cannot protect the cleric/chanter, my guess is they probably will not last very long. ESPECIALLY if the mob(s) are quad hitting in the 100's or higher. Even my 56 necro can pull a MOB off of a chanter or cleric with a cast of EB or two. And if this cant be done, a simple cast of divine aura will give your tank(s) 15 seconds or so to do some more significant damage or give your chanter time to stun so you can root or what have you....bottome line, if you are in a group and they cant taunt a mob off of the cleric, I wouldnt expect the cleric to stick around for long</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
